<br>
My friends. Most of my friends, who I had tons of, I had to leave behind. I didn't want too, but I knew if I didn't I'd feel I'm missing out on somthing. I still miss all of them dearly...<br>
<br>
My equipment and levels. The original Zildrax has 150 days played time on him. That's not easy to leave behind, and I had my epic among other things and was 4 blues from 60. I was proud of everything I learned and it was fun to play with. Despite what people say, levels are directly tied into roleplaying. You can't roleplay a really powerful Shaman if your level 5. I liked being the High Mystic of Cazic-Thule but in order to do that my level had to be very high, otherwise people just don't respect your rank. <br>
<br>
My characters personailty and history. This was very hard, the Zildrax of Morell-Thule had the best personailty, best relations and a really deep and long history forged by ingame events. I had to abandon ALL of that, as you can't come to a new server and proclaim your the &quot;High Mystic&quot; at level 1, with no powers to back you up, and no followers. Everything I developed on MT I had to give up...and it really sucked having to do that. The Zildrax who exsisted on MT will always be the &quot;real&quot; Zildrax to me.<br>
<br>
So that's why leaving MT was very hard and I always have and always will have a bit of a resentment of FV for forcing me to make that decision. I know I could have just stayed, but everything on MT started to change around FV's launch date. Besides...now the only reason I play EQ is for my guild, Skathris Ven'Sho. <br>
